examples.en: They're eagerly awaiting the big day.
We are awaiting their imminent arrival.
He is in prison awaiting execution.
They were awaiting the arrival of guests.
The army was in the field awaiting action.
Several men are awaiting trial for robbery.
We are still awaiting the final outcome of the trial.
Police are awaiting the results of a forensic examination.
They are eagerly awaiting the arrival of their wedding day.
Many trade disputes are pending, awaiting the outcome of the talks.
Murphy sat in a prison cell awaiting trial (=waiting for his trial to begin).
Electronic monitoring bracelets are sometimes used to impose a circumscription of movement on people awaiting trial.
